Introduction

Data Classification is a process in which data is categorized into different classes based on input features.

Classification is a supervised machine learning technique where:

Input data is trained using labeled datasets.
The model predicts the class/category of new data.

Examples:

Spam email detection
Disease prediction
Student result prediction
Fraud detection
Classification Algorithms

Common classification algorithms are:

Algorithm	Use
Decision Tree	Rule-based classification
Naive Bayes	Probability-based classification
K-Nearest Neighbor (KNN)	Distance-based classification
Logistic Regression	Binary classification
Support Vector Machine (SVM)	Margin-based classification
Decision Tree Classification

Decision Tree Learning is a supervised learning algorithm used for classification and prediction.

It works like a tree structure:

Root node → main condition
Internal node → decision
Leaf node → final class/output
Steps in Classification Process
Collect dataset
Split dataset into training and testing data
Train classification model
Predict output
Evaluate accuracy
Advantages
Easy to understand
Fast prediction
Handles large datasets
Useful for decision making
